gate: OPEN
sprint: S04
track: A
task: A2
title: "obs: Sentry tag upstream.timeout=hono on SearchServiceTimeoutError (#1256)"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: P1
refs:
  - CROP-front#1256
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, TYPESCRIPT]

description: |
  SearchServiceTimeoutError events land in Sentry without a distinguishing tag —
  they look like generic errors and are impossible to filter by upstream cause.
  Add `upstream.timeout=hono` tag at the throw/capture site so all hono-originated
  timeouts are instantly filterable in Sentry dashboards and alerts.

scope:
  in:
    - Locate SearchServiceTimeoutError throw/capture site(s) in crop-front
    - Add Sentry.setTag('upstream.timeout', 'hono') at each capture site
    - Unit test: SearchServiceTimeoutError thrown → Sentry.setTag called with correct args
  out:
    - Changing timeout values or retry logic
    - Any crop-parts-services or crop-search-hono changes

acceptance:
  - SearchServiceTimeoutError events in Sentry carry upstream.timeout=hono tag
  - Unit test confirms setTag is called
  - No other error types receive the tag

dep: none
output: error capture site(s) patched + unit test
